  "title": "Executive Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Quantity take-off and cost estimation.</li>\n  <li>Material ordering, budget tracking on quantity for main materials (eg: rebars, tiles etc).</li>\n  <li>Measurement, payment response, VO for subcon.</li>\n  <li>Preparing of tender submission within specific deadline.</li>\n  <li>Source, negotiate and awarding of contracts to vendors.</li>\n  <li>Tendering and contract documents administration, preparing BQ, cost estimation, control and budgeting.</li>\n  <li>Monitoring actual construction cost vs contract work quality.</li>\n  <li>Ensuring that cost is ideally managed within budget throughout the project.</li>\n  <li>Advising the project team on contractual rights and arbitration procedures when dispute arises.</li>\n  <li>Ensure meticulous assessment of costs / schedule of all projects activities.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma or Degree in Quantity Surveying.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 4-years of relevant working experience in the Construction industry.</li>\n  <li>Good with figures and an eye for details.</li>\n  <li>Good oral and written communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Ability to meet tight deadlines.</li>\n  <li>Knowledgeable about construction materials and procurement methods.</li>\n  <li>AutoCAD, Microsoft Office and Bluebeam</li>\n  <li>Good knowledge in Building Construction Works, Singapore Contracts Law and regulations will be an added advantage.</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 4,
